1
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:17,680
Master Xu,

2
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:20,039
coming personally to pick up the young lady

3
00:01:20,039 --> 00:01:21,500
is very thoughtful of you.

4
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:41,039
Mama.

5
00:01:41,039 --> 00:01:42,160
I'm not leaving.

6
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:43,560
I won't be the First Wife.

7
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:53,800
Are you trying to

8
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:57,720
put on a good show for me?

9
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:01,760
The medicine Dr. Xu gave your father

10
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,920
is German medicine.

11
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:05,320
It's worth a month of our travel expenses.

12
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:06,880
You'd better do the math.

13
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:08,400
You're lying!

14
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:10,720
Tell me,

15
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,080
what show do you want to see?

16
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,080
These two girls

17
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,240
are quite lovely.

18
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,560
Boss Qin.

19
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:20,079
You have newcomers here.

20
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,160
Why didn't you

21
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,760
let me see them first?

22
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,079
Close the door.

23
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,800
They aren't from here.

24
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,500
I have nothing to do with them.

25
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,160
Isn't that better?

26
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:47,800
I just...

27
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,520
like...

28
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:52,000
I just like

29
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,600
feisty ones like you.

30
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,579
I wonder if your teeth are strong enough.

31
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:03,800
Fine.

32
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,320
Today,

33
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:08,560
I'll play with someone else.

34
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:37,120
Didn't you go to France?

35
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,320
Where did you learn this?

36
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:40,720
There are 20,000 Chinese people in France.

37
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:46,700
Teach me later.

38
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,600
My master was a noodle maker.

39
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,980
He only taught me this.

40
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,600
What do we do now?

41
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:00,600
Freeze!

42
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,360
Central Police Station!

43
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:04,840
I heard someone is abducting women here

44
00:05:04,840 --> 00:05:06,170
and brawling in public.

45
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,720
That is a bit of an exaggeration.

46
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,800
This is a rich patron taking a girl out.

47
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,280
It's legitimate business.

48
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,520
Right.

49
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,200
This business...

50
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,080
is probably over.

51
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,280
Master Xu,

52
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:23,040
we would never lie to you.

53
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:26,400
This girl has been secretly seeing a carpenter for a long time.

54
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,120
I'm afraid

55
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,960
she is no longer a virgin.

56
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:31,200
Nonsense!

57
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:32,260
Go back inside!

58
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,280
Shall I read it to you?

59
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,970
Since we parted yesterday,

60
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,400
I have been sleepless.

61
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,130
Longing to see you in my dreams,

62
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,800
yet fearing the long night brings many dreams.

63
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:46,080
And this line.

64
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:48,560
When Golden Wind and Jade Dew meet,

65
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:51,320
it surpasses all other meetings on earth.

66
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,000
How dare you lie to me?

67
00:05:58,480 --> 00:06:00,640
You are knocking on death's door.

68
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:08,160
Move.

69
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:51,960
Bro,

70
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:53,170
what's going on?

71
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,490
A wanted poster.

72
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,080
We can basically confirm now

73
00:07:03,760 --> 00:07:05,000
that this person is

74
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,920
the killer who murdered Yan Wenjun five years ago,

75
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:07,680
Gao Xiaowen.

76
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:09,920
After Gao Xiaowen killed Yan Wenjun,

77
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,360
he went on the run.

78
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,720
Later, he returned to Lianxilou,

79
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:13,720
and two days ago,

80
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,320
he committed another crime.

81
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,400
Based on the contents of this diary

82
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:19,330
and this wood carving, we can infer

83
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,000
that the killer, Gao Xiaowen,

84
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:21,840
very likely

85
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:23,920
developed feelings for Yingtao.

86
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,320
So on the day of the crime,

87
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:28,040
when he saw the victim about to rape Yingtao,

88
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,280
he took a weapon

89
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:31,640
and entered the scene from the ceiling.

90
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,000
He killed the victim.

91
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:36,520
Then, to protect Yingtao from our suspicion,

92
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,400
he deliberately locked the wooden box.

93
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,560
After the crime, he returned to the ceiling,

94
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,560
and while no one was looking,

95
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,760
he fled Lianxi Tower.

96
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,440
So that explains

97
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:46,900
why, after the killer committed the murder,

98
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:49,520
the door bolt was still locked from the inside.

99
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,210
Do you think there's a problem?

100
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,920
I was just wondering.

101
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:06,080
Gao Xiaowen has been on the run for so many years.

102
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,740
Why did he suddenly come back?

103
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,320
Do you remember

104
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,680
when Guan Sinian read

105
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,680
those two diary entries this morning?

106
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,960
Who could remember that?

107
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:19,760
She just made it up.

108
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:21,560
The diary is right here with you.

109
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:24,100
Since we parted yesterday...

110
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,600
Sleepless nights.

111
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:27,360
Hoping to meet in dreams,

112
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:29,320
but fearing that a long night brings trouble.

113
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:31,120
I remember there was another entry.

114
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:33,159
When the golden wind and jade dew meet,

115
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,200
it is worth more than

116
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,799
countless moments on earth.

117
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,120
How could Guan Sinian

118
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,960
know what's in this diary?

119
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:48,040
Didn't she go up to deliver food?

120
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:49,120
Did she see it?

121
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:50,920
No.

122
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,640
If she just glanced at it,

123
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:54,600
how could she remember it so clearly?

124
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,480
And we all overlooked one thing.

125
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:58,520
Yingtao came to Lianxi Tower

126
00:08:58,520 --> 00:08:59,520
only a month ago.

127
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:00,800
But this diary

128
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,400
starts from four months ago.

129
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,760
This statue

130
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:10,560
isn't Yingtao.

131
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:15,960
It's Guan Sinian.

132
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,280
The ID was issued five years ago.

133
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:25,280
This statue was likely carved five years ago, too.

134
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:30,720
Go check.

135
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,280
January 7th, five years ago.

136
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,740
What was the weather like?

137
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:34,760
Heavy rain.

138
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,320
Are you sure?

139
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,120
Yes.

140
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:43,440
In the 11th year of the Republic,

141
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,880
on January 7th,

142
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,920
that night,

143
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:48,820
I gave birth to my third child.

144
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:50,720
His name was Xia Dayu.

145
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,440
This diary

146
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,400
wasn't written by Gao Xiaowen for Yingtao,

147
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:09,360
but for you, five years ago.

148
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:13,050
What is your relationship?

149
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,280
Keep practicing.

150
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:40,940
Don't stop.

151
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:42,880
Okay, Mom.

152
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:20,680
Um...

153
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,010
I'm here to fix the roof.

154
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,730
It's raining today.

155
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,320
I'll come back next time

156
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,250
to fix it for you.

157
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,640
We are lovers.

158
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,080
This morning,

159
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:02,340
why didn't you tell us?

160
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,800
You didn't ask me this morning,

161
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,600
so I didn't say anything.

162
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:12,760
So before the crime,

163
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:14,120
you were already together,

164
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:14,720
right?

165
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:16,960
We were so close.

166
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:21,040
We were about to live a different life.

167
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:27,170
Why did you bring a bug here?

168
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,530
This is no ordinary bug.

169
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:29,410
Eventually,

170
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:31,260
it will turn into a butterfly.

171
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:32,280
A butterfly?

172
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:38,880
Don't lie to me.

173
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:40,760
I'm not lying.

174
00:12:41,040 --> 00:12:41,640
I swear.

175
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,160
Really?

176
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:15,760
What did you tell him?

177
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:18,440
I told him

178
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:20,960
that if this bug

179
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:22,690
really turns into a butterfly,

180
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,450
I'd leave here with him.

181
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,160
Really?

182
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:41,800
Back then,

183
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:44,000
I saved the money I earned from singing,

184
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,120
keeping it all,

185
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:48,450
waiting for the day I could leave with him.

186
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,320
If we saved for one more month,

187
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:56,250
we'd have enough for boat tickets.

188
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,660
When we get to Tianjin,

189
00:13:58,240 --> 00:13:59,640
I'll work as a carpenter.

190
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:00,600
Then,

191
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:02,360
I'll buy you the most beautiful clothes

192
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,820
from Liangyou Pictorial.

193
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:08,880
I want to go to school.

194
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:11,480
I want to go to so many places.

195
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:15,080
No matter where you want to go,

196
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:16,080
I will go with you.

197
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:19,300
That day, Qin Xiaowan went to get Gao Xiaowen

198
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,500
to help me repair the bed beam.

199
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,400
I found out later.

200
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:27,890
Yan Wenjun didn't just lose control because of alcohol.

201
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:29,440
It was Qin Xiaowan

202
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:31,480
who auctioned my virginity to him.

203
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:33,760
She thought that

204
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:36,320
making Gao Xiaowen watch me lose my virginity

205
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,010
would make him leave me.

206
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:40,580
But what she didn't expect was

207
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,440
that Gao Xiaowen would kill for me.

208
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:47,120
After Gao Xiaowen ran away,

209
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:49,320
when did you see him again?

210
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:54,780
He didn't run away.

211
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,800
He's been here all along.

212
00:15:02,760 --> 00:15:03,800
You mean

213
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:06,490
Gao Xiaowen has been here all these years?

214
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,080
Don't cry.

215
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,730
You look better when you smile.

216
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:22,820
Stop saving up.

217
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:24,850
I can't go anywhere now.

218
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,120
I am the Boss now.

219
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:34,240
Sooner or later,

220
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:36,040
we'll save enough to leave here.

221
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,130
Then we'll buy boat tickets

222
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:40,370
and leave together.

223
00:16:40,920 --> 00:16:41,850
We'll go abroad.

224
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,740
No one will know you there.

225
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,240
I know.

226
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,400
He gave up.

227
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,160
Later,

228
00:16:58,360 --> 00:16:59,480
as time went by,

229
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,800
we actually got used to it.

230
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:05,220
I went up to keep him company every night.

231
00:17:05,839 --> 00:17:07,720
Sometimes, when everyone was asleep,

232
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:10,450
he'd come out to the courtyard for some fresh air.

233
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,520
I thought life would go on like this forever.

234
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:17,240
But I didn't expect that that night,

235
00:17:18,359 --> 00:17:19,520
he would kill again.

236
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:21,760
He killed for you back then.

237
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:23,180
I can understand that.

238
00:17:23,359 --> 00:17:24,890
It was because he loved you.

239
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:26,560
But now,

240
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:28,840
why did he have to kill again for Yingtao?

241
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:31,760
Maybe I'm the only one who understands him.

242
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,240
He's a good man.

243
00:17:36,320 --> 00:17:38,280
He'd never leave someone to die.

244
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:40,520
Guan Sinian.

245
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,400
I know you hope he's alive.

246
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,880
So you have to tell us

247
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:47,080
everything you know.

248
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:49,490
Where is Gao Xiaowen right now?

249
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:03,040
I want to know where he is, too.

250
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:07,080
Why did he leave me behind?

251
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,440
Why didn't he take me with him?
